{"id":1693693,"retrievedAt":"2026-05-13T13:30:33.749Z","response":{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":null,"belongs_to_collection":null,"budget":0,"genres":[{"id":99,"name":"Documentary"}],"homepage":"http://www.bockhorstproductions.com/product.php?prodID=18","id":1693693,"imdb_id":null,"origin_country":["US"],"original_language":"en","original_title":"Pursuing Beauty: The Architecture of Bernard Maybeck","overview":"PURSUING BEAUTY: The Architecture of Bernard Maybeck tells the story of a 19th century romantic who used 20th century materials to create buildings that speak across time. The body of work that Maybeck created is remarkably diverse - by turns antique and modern, rustic and refined, theatrical and sublime. His projects reveal an original vision, a reverence for nature, a commitment to community, and a deep and abiding love of beauty. Over twenty of Maybeck's important works are featured in Pursuing Beauty, including his best known project, the Palace of Fine Arts in San Francisco. Also seen are Hearst Hall at the University of California; Wyntoon in Siskiyou County: the George Boke, Andrew Lawson, J.H. Senger, and Albert Schneider houses, all in Berkeley; the Samuel Goslinsky and Leon Roos houses in San Francisco; First Church of Christ Scientist in Berkeley; the Guy Hyde Chick House in Oakland; and several buildings at Principia College in Elsah, Illinois.","popularity":0,"poster_path":"/6HVmL2q8zKT0rn0uvcTrlmC7PqG.jpg","production_companies":[{"id":298319,"logo_path":null,"name":"Paul Bockhorst Productions","origin_country":""}],"production_countries":[],"release_date":"2012-01-01","revenue":0,"runtime":86,"softcore":false,"spoken_languages":[],"status":"Released","tagline":"","title":"Pursuing Beauty: The Architecture of Bernard Maybeck","video":false,"vote_average":0,"vote_count":0,"alternative_titles":{"titles":[]},"credits":{"cast":[{"adult":false,"gender":0,"id":6209233,"known_for_department":"Acting","name":"Richard Doyle","original_name":"Richard Doy